#: view/search-solr/admin/core/help-index-names.phtml:12
msgid "About index names"
msgstr ""

#: view/search-solr/admin/core/help-index-names.phtml:14
msgid ""
"The indices of the default Solr configuration work with names and suffixes "
"matching type:"
msgstr ""

#: view/search-solr/admin/core/help-index-names.phtml:16
msgid "\"_t\" and \"_txt\" are used to store words individually."
msgstr ""

#: view/search-solr/admin/core/help-index-names.phtml:17
msgid "\"_s\" and \"_ss\" are used to store whole string."
msgstr ""

#: view/search-solr/admin/core/help-index-names.phtml:18
msgid "\"_i\" and \"_is\" are used to store integers."
msgstr ""

#: view/search-solr/admin/core/help-index-names.phtml:19
msgid "\"_dt\" and \"_dts\" are used to store dates."
msgstr ""

#: view/search-solr/admin/core/help-index-names.phtml:20
msgid ""
"\"_ancestor_path\" and \"_descendent_path\" are used to store structures."
msgstr ""

#: view/search-solr/admin/core/help-index-names.phtml:22
msgid "The choice of type depends on what you need for a metadata:"
msgstr ""

#: view/search-solr/admin/core/help-index-names.phtml:24
msgid "For global searches, indices should be \"_t\" and \"_txt\"."
msgstr ""

#: view/search-solr/admin/core/help-index-names.phtml:25
msgid ""
"For simple filters and facets, indices should be a multiple whole values "
"(\"_ss\", \"_is\" and \"_dts\")."
msgstr ""

#: view/search-solr/admin/core/help-index-names.phtml:26
msgid "For sort, it should be a single value (\"_s\", \"_i\" and \"_dt\")."
msgstr ""

#: view/search-solr/admin/core/help-index-names.phtml:27
msgid ""
"For bounce links, it should be multiple values formatted for linking "
"(\"_link_ss\")."
msgstr ""

#: view/search-solr/admin/core/help-index-names.phtml:28
msgid ""
"For main autocompletion (\"à-la-google search\"), \"_txt\" should be used. "
"There is a default field \"suggest_txt\" that groups \"_txt\" fields."
msgstr ""

#: view/search-solr/admin/core/help-index-names.phtml:29
msgid ""
"For autocompletion in filters, you may use \"_ss\" for short values and "
"\"_txt\" for long ones. Here, autocompletion in filters is generally useless "
"for long values."
msgstr ""

#: view/search-solr/admin/core/help-index-names.phtml:30
msgid ""
"\"_ancestor_path\" and \"_descendent_path\" are generally used for search "
"and facets, generally with a thesaurus, a classification scheme, or "
"geographic names."
msgstr ""

#: view/search-solr/admin/core/help-index-names.phtml:32
msgid ""
"Other indices are available for complex cases. Solr should be configured "
"first if more types are needed."
msgstr ""

